						<summary>

						<p>The beginning of the inscription is lost. It records the gift of land, by the same chief mentioned in No. 21, for the supply of offerings to Subrahmaṇya-piḷḷaiyār and Kshētrapāla-pillaiyār. Signatories like Sundarapāṇḍyaṉ, Uttamapāṇḍyaṉ etc., are mentioned at the end of the record.</p>						

						</summary>
